,Not Recommended,249950,16215059,"Posted: 5 June, 2015",all,TheSpeedOfRound,"Pretty dissapointed, and confused as to why the review here are so positive. I bought this game with a friend to enjoy a simple dungeon crawler, but it really failed to meet my already low expectations. Here are a few of the problems I found with this game:Too easy. Probably the biggest issue was that it was never a challenge once you get a couple levels up. Bigger issue is that it dosnt seem to be balanced for multiplater at all, so the same amount of MOBS split between two people makes it twice as easy.Not enough divercity. In each dungeon there is 3 or 4 enemy types that you will kill over and over. There all the same brain dead ""move to player and attack"" AI, nothing really changes the game up to much. I've seen worse mob assortment, but in a game where all you do is grind, it becomes really tiresome.Equipment has the same issues as well, theres a few different types of armor and weapon, but you'll stick to one and use it and it's hight stat varients for basically the entire game.The dungeon puzzles are all the same drawn out push rocks around ala pokemon and do nothing other than pad the games play time.Over all this game was a very boring and stale experience. Only play it if you've never really played a dungeon crawler before and your tastes are pretty simple, and even then it's not really worth the $17 price tag."
