,Recommended,249950,18670613,"Posted: 24 October, 2015",all,ATBPsycold,"I really enjoy this game! I find it to be a great blend of Action RPG and Dungeon Crawler.  The game is blocky, but there is no digging, block gathering, or sleeping at night!Quick Rundown:  You start the game and can customize your look to some extent, ie dwarf, elf, human, wolf, kobold, male, female, colors etc.  You then get to choose your starting gear.  Feel free to take whatever looks cool because there are no classes in this game.  All skills are open to all characters.  For example I have a warrior that has magic shields and can heal others.  Both abilities are in the ""Mage"" skill tree but they lend themselves to melee heroes very well!You enter the game to find yourself in a dungeon tutorial that lasts all of 2-3 minutes, easy stuff here ladies and gents!  The storyline after the tutorial is amusing and fun but rather weak. In all honesty the game doesn't need much story as it is an exploration and action game.  You will spend most of your time looking for gems and loots!  And there is an immense amount of LOOTS! The gems are used at workbenches to socket items and to upgrade your weapons and armor with various magical and nonmagical abilities.  The trash items you collect can be crafted and combined with your ""good"" items to imbue them with higher levels and new properties.I thoroughly enjoy playing this game with my kids and wife and have no problem with boredom or it getting old.  There are modes of endless dungeons for leveling purposes or there is a story mode.  Multiplayer is fun and can be challenging but it is fun to see different character builds and each team of 4 is immensely different depending on the unique abilities and play styles of the players involved.Controls       10/10 Mouse/KB , Xbox, twin stick, or single stick controllers are supported!Graphics      7/10 Voxel but charming and fun.Sound          8/10 No complaints.  Anime type battle sounds.Gameplay    9/10 Hack n Slash, Multiple kinds of magic, pets, multiplayer coop, endless loot!Replayability 10/10 Each game is randomly generated.  You have options to reset world or keep it!This game has a very classic feel to it, much like if Gauntlet and Zelda were mashed up and spiced with a little Torchlight II.  This game probably isn't for the serious gamer but for casual gamers or younger crowd this game is golden! I highly recommend this game.8.8/10 on the casual gamer scale.This was never intended to be a blockbuster game, no pun intended,  but you do get a lot of bang for your buck."
